Generic info on FN SPR's per FN's website:


FN Special Police Rifles (SPR) are based on the legendary Pre-’64 Model 70-design action with a massive external claw extractor for Controlled Round Feed, blade ejection, the original twolever trigger and a three-position safety. All models have cold hammer-forged MIL -SPEC barrels with hard-chromed bores, and are held to +/- .001" headspace to produce and maintain one minute of angle (1 MOA ) accuracy, making them natural choices for long-range target shooting and competition. A one-piece steel MIL -STD 1913 rail with an additional 20 MOA of elevation is factory-installed. FN SPR rifles are fitted into matte black McMillan™ fiberglass stocks. Thompson Center Hawkens Muzzel Load Rifle - New – Test Fired Only 

History
In 1815 Jacob Hawken established a gun shop in the village of St. Louis. Jacob’s brother, Samuel, joined him in 1822. The Hawken brothers established a reputation for manufacturing excellent Muzzleloading Rifles. Their claim to fame was the "plains rifles". The Plains Rifle was what their customers needed when they ascended the Missouri River in search of Beaver, a quality gun, light enough to carry all the time and capable of knocking down big targets at long range.

They called their Rifles "Rocky Mountain Rifles". Rifles Stamped “J&S Hawken St. Louis” were sought after throughout the rapidly expanding frontier among trappers and mountain men. In 1849 Jacob Hawken died and rifles were marked S. Hawken. A number of famous men were said to have owned Hawken Rifles, including: Jim Bridger, Kit Carson, Joseph Meek and Theodore Roosevelt.

Undoubtedly the most copied rifle in the history of firearms, the T/C Hawken was designed for the American shooter. This is a top quality firearm—every bit as fine as the one your great, great granddaddy carried across his saddle pommel or packed along on the wagon train. It captures the romance of the original but it is manufactured to standards of quality control that were unheard of in the early 1800’s. The proper use of the investment casting, improved methods of hardening parts and deep hole drilling, the use of continuous Magnaflux process to guard against imperfections in the steel itself coupled to our constant attention to min./max. tolerances is what allows us to offer a lifetime Warranty! Thompson Center arms manufacture the finest quality muzzleloading firearms available.

It has a double triggers; the rear trigger is a "set" trigger. When the rear trigger is pulled, the hammer does not fall but rather the action "sets" the front trigger, the front trigger becoming a "hair trigger," tripped with a light touch. When the front trigger is used without using the rear "set" trigger, it requires a firm pull.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Bulgarian AK 74 parts kit + ammo
postcontent:
I have an AK 74 parts kit that I had full intentions of putting together, but my free time is dwindling and I have so many other projects. 
So here it is:
This is a BULGARIAN AK 74 parts kit with all matching numbers.  I have two trigger group systems, one regular G2 and the other is a FULL AUTO.  The full auto fire control group is 100% legal and will function as a semi auto only, so long as you don't drill the two holes in the receiver.  This is a cool legal loophole if you are into the SHTF preparation. The Bulgarian 74s are much much better quality than the Polish and Russian.  I have assembled a few of these over the years and they are easy and very forgiving, just a bit time consuming.  Expect 5 to 6 hours of labor on your first time.  It is an easy build, just time consuming if you do it right.  Also this kit has all of the legal US parts and a new barrel.  Most kits that you see online do not have these parts (you end up spending 150+ to get), are usually missing the barrel (100+ as well), and don't have the matching numbers.  I am not trying to make money off of this deal, just clearing my project list up. But if you do build this, you can easily sell Bulgarian AK74s for 8-900.  Check it out on Gunbroker
There are also about 400 rounds of ammo for it included in the deal.  The 5.45x39 is much more fun to shoot in my opinion than the 7.62x39 and is a wicked round.

This is a 2nd Generation Smith with the BEST trigger I've ever experienced on a Smith. DA/SA with decocker and mag safety. Adjustable rear sight. The early version of the 639 is widely considered to be the best 9mm S&W ever made.  It was manufactured only 2 years and they do not come up for sale very often.  Later versions with the squared trigger guard and ambi decocker are of lesser quality.  This is one of the best 9mm pistols you can own, and I will regret parting with it.
